article.description: — Chris Ledlum had 17 points and 11 rebounds to lead Harvard to a 62-54 win over Holy Cross on Sunday.
article.headline: Ledlum double-double leads Harvard past Holy Cross 62-54
article.linkText: Ledlum double-double leads Harvard past Holy Cross 62-54
article.story: BOSTON -- — Chris Ledlum had 17 points and 11 rebounds to lead Harvard to a 62-54 win over Holy Cross on Sunday. Noah Kirkwood had 11 points for Harvard (7-4). Samuel Silverstein added six rebounds. Kyrell Luc had 17 points for the Crusaders (2-10), whose losing streak reached six games. Caleb Kenney added 10 points and 11 rebounds. Louth-M Coulibaly had 10 rebounds. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
